{"accepted":[{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Solution to variant problem.","id":"vf_6325f815af5addde","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #251: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Is\\[\\sum \\frac{p_n}{2^n}\\]irrational? (Here $p_n$ is the $n$th prime.) Current best: Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er58b} proved that $\\sum \\frac{p_n^k}{n!}$ is irrational for every $k\\geq 1$. In \\cite{Er88c} he further conjectures that $\\sum \\frac{p_n^k}{2^n}$ is irrational for every $k$, and that if $g_n\\geq 2$ and $g_n=o(p_n)$ then\\[\\sum_{n=1}^\\infty \\frac{p_n}{g_1\\cdots g_n}\\]is irrational. Prize: no. OEIS: A098990. Tags: irrationality, number theory.","id":"vf_7ce74272755c55f9","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos251.erdos_251 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos251.erdos_251.","id":"vf_a480223749768d6e","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/251.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_6325f815af5addde","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:251","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_7ce74272755c55f9","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:251","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_a480223749768d6e","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144